n admission  the Office of International Services  OIS  will request the submission of the required OIS Documents in order to prepare the proper immigration document  I    DS       Submission can be done by logging into your application summary page and following the instructions for uploading documents  As part of your OIS Documents  international students must submit detailed financial statements before a Form I    DS      can be processed  These statements should include the amounts and sources of funds available for educational expenses in the United States NOTE  Students are not required to submit the OIS Documents until they have been admitted to UIC  However  submission prior to admission will help expedite the processing of the I    or DS      and students are welcome to do so at any time after submitting their application For the most up to date information regarding your admission  please check your Undergraduate or  Graduate application status online Undergraduate  Graduate Submitting the OIS Documents for your Initial I    or DS      All international students who will be sponsored by the University of Illinois at Chicago  UIC  including those students who will transfer their immigration record to UIC  must submit a completed UIC Declaration and Certification of Finances  DCF  financial documentation  and a copy of the biographical page in your passport in order for you to obtain the I    or DS      necessary to obtain your student visa  To fulfill your "OIS Documents" requirement  please submit the documents by logging into your Undergraduate or Graduate Application Summary Page  Undergraduate Graduate Declaration and Certification of Finances  DCF estimated expenses Which account types are acceptable for the I    DS      request  Financial statements must be signed or stamped by a bank official  and show a current balance  Students may be contacted to submit additional proof of authentication  if needed  Statements should not be issued more than six months from the date of request  Documents must be in English  or include a certified English translation The following is a summary of acceptable sources of funding  estimated expenses Please click on the following links to view sample financial documents to assist you in submitting proper documentation to our office Sample Checking or Savings Bank Letter   Sample Checking or Savings Bank Letter   Sample Term Deposit Bank Letter The following is a summary of account types OIS does NOT accept  How long does it take to process my I    DS       Once the Office of International Services receives your complete I    DS      request and your admission has been confirmed  please allow up to   business days for processing  When your I    DS      is ready you will receive an email from OIS outlining your shipping options for your immigration document Options include  How can I check the status of my I    or DS       Upon admission  you can check if your I    or DS      has been mailed to you by logging into  your Undergraduate or  Graduate Application Summary Page Undergraduate  Graduate If you have questions about the information in your student portal  please email newintl uic edu newintl uic edu Obtaining your F   or J   Visa Stamp Once you have received your I    DS      from UIC you can take the next step which is to apply for an F   J   visa at the nearest U S  Embassy or Consulate  For an outline of this process  please visit our Travel   Visas page Travel   Visas page How can I request an I    DS      for my dependent  A spouse or unmarried  minor child  under age     is eligible for a dependent visa  F   or J    Extended family members such as parents and siblings are not eligible for a dependent visa To request an I    DS      for your dependent  Declaration and Certification of Finances  DCF  Form What if I intend to study at UIC on a visa type other than F   or J    If you already hold valid visa status other than F   J   nthat allows for study in the U S  and wish to remain in that status nwhile studying at UIC  please upload the following to your Undergraduate or Graduate Application Summary Page  Undergraduate Graduate Declaration and Certification of Finances  DCF Upon receipt of your OIS Documents  OIS will update your nApplication Summary Page accordingly  International students holding nvisas other than F   J   are still required to complete the Immigration Check in process with OIS and are strongly encouraged to attend New International Student Orientation Immigration Check in New International Student Orientation How do I defer my admission to a later semester  Students may decide to defer their admission to the University of Illinois at Chicago for many reasons  such as a delay in obtaining a visa or personal reasons  If you would like to defer your admission to a later semester  you must contact your academic department  Your academic department will inform you of the proper procedures to defer your admission  Please review registration requirements before deferring admission to a subsequent semester Please contact the Office of International Services  OIS  at newintl uic edu to inform us of your plans for deferral  If your deferral is approved by the Office of Admissions  OIS will review your financial documents  If your financial documents were issued within the last   months  OIS will amend your immigration record and start dates on your I    DS      and mail you a new I    DS       If your financial documents are more than   months old  OIS will request updated financial documents before issuing the I    DS       If you are funded through your department  OIS will request an updated letter from your department newintl uic edu Email newintl uic edu if you have any questions about deferring your admission newintl uic edu Skip Nav UICOIS Navigation Menu Home About OIS Students Prospective Students General Information Graduate Admissions Undergraduate Admissions Obtaining an Initial I    DS      Declaration and Cer